{
  "stem": "27390.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My older-- I had an old sister.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Her name was Rachel.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was two years older than me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was the middle child.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then I have a younger brother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "His name is Yitzhak.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he lives-- he's alive.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He survived with me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he lives now in Israel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, what I can remember from my childhood, it was a very happy childhood.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We, we had a normal childhood.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as far as I knew, my parents got on very well amongst themselves.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we had a large-- lots of cousins, and uncles, and aunts.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my, my, my par-- my father's parents were still alive.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They lived in Lodz.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But my mother's parents, they came from a little town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was called Szydlow in Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Polish, I think it was spelled S-Z-Y-D-O-V.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Szydlow.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my-- my grandfather, I was told, was the-- the shochet in that little town.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was-- a shochet is a-- is a-- a ritual slaughterer.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He has to be a well learned man, otherwise he can't perform the-- the ritual killing of the animals or, or birds.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was usually well-respected in the community.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was usually the second most respected person after the rabbi in the town.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So-- and I'm named after-- his name was Alexander, and I'm named after him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because as you know amongst Jews, we do not name-- amongst Ashkenazi Jews-- we do not name the children if the people are still alive.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So because he was already dead when I was born, so they named me after him.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were very orthodox.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Although my father did not have a beard, which in Poland it was very unusual amongst Orthodox Jews.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They usually had beards.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father was clean-shaven because he was a businessman.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
